# Quest Board System

## Architecture

- `QuestBoardManager` is the single entry point for all board operations. Accessed via `registryAccess().registry(RegistryKey.MANAGER).manager(McRPGManagerKey.QUEST_BOARD)`.
- The template engine (`QuestTemplateEngine`) is **stateless** тАФ all state is passed as arguments; registries injected at construction.
- `QuestDefinition` is **immutable** and shared across quest instances. Per-player state lives in `QuestInstance`.
- `BoardOffering` tracks state transitions: `AVAILABLE` тЖТ `ACCEPTED` тЖТ `COMPLETED`/`EXPIRED`.

## Template Conditions

`TemplateCondition` is the extensible interface for gating template elements. Built-in types:
- `RarityCondition` тАФ rarity range gate
- `ChanceCondition` тАФ probabilistic inclusion
- `VariableCondition` тАФ checks resolved variable values
- `CompoundCondition` тАФ `ALL`/`ANY` logical combinator
- `PermissionCondition` тАФ player permission check (player-dependent)
- `CompletionPrerequisiteCondition` тАФ quest completion count gate (player-dependent)

Player-dependent conditions require a `ConditionContext` built via `forPersonalGeneration()` (with player UUID + completion history). During shared offering generation, `forTemplateGeneration()` is used and player-dependent conditions return `false` when player fields are absent, causing gated elements to be excluded from shared generation. Template-level prerequisites are evaluated during personal offering generation via `QuestPool.getEligibleTemplates()` with a `ConditionContext.forPrerequisiteCheck()` context; templates with prerequisites are excluded from shared boards entirely.

Third-party conditions are registered via `TemplateConditionContentPack`.

## Reward Entries

`QuestDefinition` stores `List<QuestRewardEntry>` internally. Each entry wraps a `QuestRewardType` with an optional `RewardFallback`. The backward-compatible `getRewards()` method unwraps to `List<QuestRewardType>`. Use `getRewardEntries()` when fallback evaluation is needed.

Distribution tier rewards use `DistributionRewardEntry` which additionally carries `PotBehavior`, `RemainderStrategy`, `minScaledAmount`, and `topCount`.

## Condition Context Sites

| Factory Method | When Used |
|---|---|
| `forTemplateGeneration()` | Shared offering generation (no player context) |
| `forPersonalGeneration()` | Personal offering generation (has player UUID + completion history) |
| `forPrerequisiteCheck()` | Template/category eligibility before generation |
| `forRewardGrant()` | Fallback reward evaluation at grant time |

## Key Patterns

- **3-phase async pattern**: Board operations that touch DB + main thread use: Phase 1 (DB executor: load), Phase 2 (main thread: generate + fire events), Phase 3 (DB executor: persist).
- **Deterministic seeding**: `PersonalOfferingGenerator.computeSeed()` ensures same player sees same offerings within a rotation.
- **Orphaned state repair**: `validateOfferingStates()` detects ACCEPTED offerings with no active `QuestInstance` and transitions them to EXPIRED.
- **Concurrent acceptance**: Per-offering `synchronized` locks via `ConcurrentHashMap<UUID, Object>` prevent race conditions.

## Anti-Patterns

- **Never store mutable state on `QuestRewardType` instances** тАФ configured instances are shared across quest definitions.
- **Never call `forTemplateGeneration()` for personal offerings** тАФ use `forPersonalGeneration()` so player-dependent conditions evaluate correctly.
- **Never access DB on main thread** in board operations тАФ use the 3-phase async pattern.
- **Never hard-code rarity names** тАФ always use `NamespacedKey` looked up from `QuestRarityRegistry`.

## Configuration Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `quest-board/board.yml` | Board settings, rarity definitions, rotation config |
| `quest-board/templates/*.yml` | Quest template definitions |
| `quest-board/categories.yml` | Board slot category definitions |
| `en_gui.yml` | Quest board GUI localization keys |
